## Never / Always

### Never
- [ ] Hardcode API keys, tokens, passwords, or secrets in source files
- [ ] Store sensitive data in `localStorage`, `sessionStorage`, or `UserDefaults`
- [ ] Call the database directly from controllers, routes, or UI components
- [ ] Add a new dependency (npm/pip/gem/etc.) without explicit approval in the current session
- [ ] Disable SSL/TLS certificate verification, even in test environments
- [ ] Log request or response bodies that may contain user PII
- [ ] Catch and silently swallow errors — always log or surface them
- [ ] Leave `// TODO` or `// FIXME` comments in committed code without a linked ticket

### Always
- [ ] Hash passwords using bcrypt with cost factor ≥ 12
- [ ] Validate and sanitize all external input at the system boundary
- [ ] Write error messages the user can act on — not raw exception text
- [ ] Add a retry/refresh affordance for all network-dependent UI states
- [ ] Follow the existing naming conventions (see `/src` for reference)
- [ ] Run `<LINT_COMMAND>` before considering a task complete

